title: The Hidden Hand
creator: E.D.E.N. Southworth.
description: LibriVox recording of The Hidden Hand by E.D.E.N. Southworth. Read by Bridget "If you will listen to this book, you will meet a cast of unforgettable characters, as different from one another as the sun and moon. But they have one thing in common - all of them hide many, many secrets. The plot of this book is full of twists which may leave you guessing until the end. Bridget's lively reading adds much to the joy of listening to this book." (Summary by Stav Nisser) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. reviews.reviewbody:
I liked it a lot but it was hard to listen to, so tragic are many of the occurences in the book.

A nurse is kidnapped and delivers a set of twins in secret.  She is begged by the mother to take one of the twins with her and 'save her.'  Years later, the nurse on her deathbed tells her story to a local military man, hoping to find justice for the child she raised who is now without a friend in the world.  

The man determines to save the child and see to it that justice is done.  Thus begins an up and down story where just as you think things will be okay, they take a tragic turn for the worse again.  It was an emotional rollercoaster.  

Reading was very good.

This was a really good story.  I think the hidden hand could also mean the hidden hand of God as there was often divine intervention going on.  Although not a religious person myself, I thought that the religious undertones were done very well.  The story is riveting and I truly enjoyed it.  I have listened to a few other narrations by Bridget and she does a nice job.  Her voice is well suited to the character of Cap.
